<main id="content" class="content"> <header> <h1 class="title">List Spacing in Org Mode with Enumitem</h1>
 <p class="subtitle" role="doc-subtitle">Feb 01, 2023 00:00</p>
</header> <p>
I like to use the LaTeX package enumitem to eliminate the spacing in lists. To do this globally, add the following to the Org mode headers:
</p>

 <div class="org-src-container">
 <pre class="src src-org"> <span class="org-org-meta-line">#+LaTeX_HEADER: \usepackage{enumitem}</span>
 <span class="org-org-meta-line">#+LaTeX_HEADER: \setlist{nosep}</span>
</pre>
</div>

 <p>
If you also don’t want your lists to be indented, use 
</p>

 <div class="org-src-container">
 <pre class="src src-org"> <span class="org-org-meta-line">#+LaTeX_HEADER: \setlist{nosep,wide}</span>
</pre>
</div>

 <p>
These global options can be overridden for individual lists by putting something like this immediately before the list begins:
</p>

 <div class="org-src-container">
 <pre class="src src-org"> <span class="org-org-meta-line">#+ATTR_LaTeX: :options [itemsep=1em]</span>
</pre>
</div>

 <p>
This will put a space equal to the width of an upper-case “M” between each list item. 
</p>


